  "prompt": "What is reliance jio?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio, commonly known as Jio, is a telecommunications company in India and a subsidiary of Reliance Industries, which is one of the largest conglomerates in India. Launched in 2016, Jio revolutionized the telecommunications sector in the country by offering affordable 4G LTE services, leading to a significant increase in internet penetration across India. Jio's entry into the market resulted in intense competition, which drove down prices for mobile data and voice services nationwide.\n\nJio offers a wide range of services, including mobile telephony, broadband, and digital services. It has expanded its offerings to include JioFiber, a high-speed fiber broadband service, as well as various digital applications and platforms for entertainment, news, and financial services. Over the years, Jio has also ventured into developing its own smartphones and other electronic devices. The company is known for its innovative approach and has played a pivotal role in transforming the digital landscape in India.",
